description: From Latin praeponderatus, past participle of praeponderāre (“to outweigh”).

verbs.description: preponderate (third-person singular simple present preponderates, present participle preponderating, simple past and past participle preponderated)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To outweigh; to be heavier than; to exceed in weight.
(transitive) To overpower by stronger or moral power.
(transitive, obsolete) To cause to prefer; to incline; to decide.
(intransitive) To exceed in weight or influence; hence, to predominate.
